answers.body_markdown:
First you don&#39;t need to mess with the value of the input control, there is a `placeholder` attribute you can use for that:

**HTML**
```
&lt;input size=&quot;50&quot; placeholder=&quot;&quot; name=&quot;SearchValue&quot; id=&quot;SearchValue&quot;&gt;
```

**Javascript**

```
window.onload = onPageLoad();

function onPageLoad() {
  var url = document.location.href;

  if (url.indexOf(&quot;sometext&quot;) &gt; -1) {
    $(&quot;#SearchValue&quot;).attr(&quot;placeholder&quot;, &quot;Search by keyword or catalogue number&quot;);
  }
  else {
    $(&quot;#SearchValue&quot;).attr(&quot;placeholder&quot;, &quot;Search by keyword&quot;);
  }
}
```

You can try it here: https://zikro.gr/dbg/html/test.html?sometext

